The 10% drop in housing starts from 1724 to 1549 in May is concerning - probably due to a combination of decreasing buyer pool with increased borrowing rates, increased material & labor costs, with continued supply chain issues? Can't forget other random factors as well. Reran forecasts using an ARMA(1,1) and SARIMA(1,1,1) model and aggregated with selected peers. Housing starts have a long way to fall in order to match up with home buyer sentiment. This is a very long-term market that takes a lot of time to adjust to changing trends. A building project can easily be 18 months from planning to permit to final end of construction.

Reran my forecasts using Holt-Winter's, ARMA, and SARIMA. Based on this, I am concerned that there may be more uncertainty in the final forecast than I see the crowd accounting for. While these are literally no more than "chimp" reference class models, it is worth taking note of, especially early in the forecasting process. I am moderating my bets accordingly, until more data is available on the FRED site.
